    <h1>The Shoeless Tech Genius</h1>
    <p>
      Growing up in rural Kenya, Kelvin Doe built his first radio transmitter out of scrap at just 13. With no formal training and limited resources, he taught himself engineering through trial and error. Often seen barefoot, Kelvin became known as the “shoeless tech genius” in his community.
    </p>
    <p>
